  • Two 108kg storage capacity trolleys, 17kg capacity head

  • Polyethylene moulded trolleys
  • Durable castors

 

Benefits

  • Suitable for ice collection and transport
  • Polyethylene insulation designed for maximum ice retention
  • internally insulated to assure the perfect ice conservation
  • Durable stainless steel exterior
  • Perfect all in one ice storage and transport solution

 

Warranty: 12 months

Name: Brema 13G Ice Maker with Push-Button Dispenser and Bin. 44Kg Production 12Kg Storage
Description:
Brema's Special Series DSS42A 13g Ice Cube Maker produces 44kg per day of artisan crystalline ice cubes with 12kg of storage capacity while also featuring a push button ice dispenser. The elegant and impactful 13g Cube maximises profits by holding its temperature and melts vastly slower than its competitors, meaning your beverage on the rocks truly stays on the rocks.

 

Connection: 240v 10a

Energy: 450W

Type of Ice: 13g

Production (in 24 hours): 42kg

Storage: 12kg

 

Features

  • 42kg per day ice production, 12kg of storage plus push button ice dispensing
  • Electromechanical operation that does not use Printed Circuit Boards
  • Hospital grade stainless steel exterior and interior that never rusts or corrodes
  • Air cooling system is rated at 21°C ambient and 15°C water
  • Stainless steel spray arms and internal filters are all detachable

 

Benefits

  • Comes with its own water filter & pressure limiting valve, saving you over $300
  • No tools required or panels removed to clean spray arms and filters, meaning quick easy cleaning
  • 21°C ambient and 15°C water ratings give an accurate production average for the Australian climate
  • individual cube moulds gradually build cubes as it freezes for long lasting crystalline cubes
  • Push button ice dispenser offers the perfect solution for bars and means no direct contact with ice

 

Specifications

  • Volts: 240
  • Amps: 10

 

Warranty (Parts/Labour): 24 / 24 months

  • Powerful cylindrical evaporator and ice scraper system

 

Benefits

  • Produces fl at ice fl akes between 5°C and 10°C for maximum longevity of foods
  • 21°C ambient and 15°C water ratings give an accurate production average for the Australian climate
  • Comes with its own water filter & pressure limiting valve, saving you over $300
  • Semi hermetic compressor used to ensure maximum output in a compact sized unit
  • The perfect solution for meat, fish, and dairy industries, supermarkets and transport companies

 

Specifications
